        <h3>
            <div class="field field--name-name field--type-string field--label-hidden field__item">Why marine turtles are so important</div>
      </h3>

            <div class="clearfix text-formatted field field--name-field-slice-text field--type-text-long field--label-hidden field__item"><p>They might not look like voracious killers, but turtles are actually important predators that help to keep ocean food chains healthy.</p>
<p>For example, hawksbill turtles eat lots of sea sponges, which would otherwise out-compete reef-building corals. So the turtles help to protect the coral reefs, which are crucial for the survival of many other creatures.</p>
<p>The leatherback turtle is a big eater of jellyfish, which helps stops the jellyfish depleting fish stocks – which benefits other animals in the food chain, as well as people.</p>
</div>


